From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Subject: cameraisp: WPE/DIP probe + init fixes for Volla X23 native boot

The vidofnir mt6789.dts has DT issues for WPE+DIP camera subsystems:
- wpe_a@15011000 / wpe_b@15811000: bare nodes (compatible/reg/interrupts only)
- imgsys_config@15020000: mediatek,larb has only 1 phandle but driver expects 2

Original behaviour deadlocks PID 1 (insmod) and trips SoC watchdog ~30s later.

Fixes:

1. WPE_probe + DIP_probe: early-return -ENODEV when mediatek,larb is absent.
   Avoids pm_runtime_enable + of_find_device_by_node(NULL) on bare DT nodes
   (of_find_device_by_node(NULL) returns a NON-NULL garbage pointer that
   the WARN_ON check fails to catch).

2. DIP_probe: stop dereferencing NULL phandles.  Original code passes
   node_larb9/11 directly to of_find_device_by_node even when of_parse_phandle
   returned NULL.  Add NULL-checks; leave dip_devs->larb11 as NULL — its
   only consumer is conditional on DIP_IMG_MFB_DIP / DIP_IMG_DIP2 clocks
   being present, which they aren't on this device.

3. WPE_Init + DIP_Init: temporarily disable cmdqCoreRegisterCB +
   register_pm_notifier under VOLLAX23_BISECT.  These calls deadlock
   on this kernel for reasons not yet root-caused; the rest of probe
   + chardev creation works fine without them.  Camera works at reduced
   level (no GCE/MDP suspend integration, no pm suspend hooks).

4. pr_emerg bisection markers retained for future debug.

After this patch + chmod 666 on /dev/camera-* (separate ueventd commit) +
the matching init.x23.cfg insmod chain, the Halium MTK HAL gets past the
original /dev/camera-rsc and /dev/camera-dip blocks and into P1Node /
P2Node configuration.  Frame delivery is still blocked further downstream
(IspDrv_B::setLCE_D1 SEGV — userspace HAL hits a NULL deref while the
"set tpipe mem info" kernel ioctl fails — see phase_n12_camera_modulemap.md).

Signed-off-by: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>

